MOSCOW â€“ Russia produced 17.84 t of gold in January, up from 15.67 t in the same period in 2018, the Finance Ministry said on Wednesday. Production for the period included 14.11 t of mined gold compared with 12.26 t a year ago, the Ministry said. Silver production totalled 66.50 t in January, down from 97.92 t in the same period of 2018.